commit_message: default barcodes should be empty list
fix bug when there are no barcodes
Fixed cPreprocess again for MiSeq files
Added align_bwa.py script and cleaned up code in all the scripts
updated documentation and fixed some docstrings. Removed broken cTubes extension and merged it back into tubes/__init__.py
Actually fixed preprocess_reads this time. Uses a fix 100k buffer for each fastq field

bugfixes for preprocess.py, w/ paired-end reads. fixed --no-clipping
mode for NCBI-compliant output
No longer trim trailing Ns from reads. Breaks NCBI guidelines

Updated analyze.py to work with MACS2 peaks files, and added a
--bysummit flag for analysis about peak summit. Bumped to version
0.9.6.0

Possibly fixed aligned.py problem with single-end BAM files. Not sure
what else is changed
Implemented better file pairing and require user input when ambiguous
work in progress, adding support for bowtie2

Updated call_peaks, setup to fix problems 0.9.4.5

Introduced align2.py to get bowtie2 working

Updated alignments to support counter-references

updated macs2, fixed to use new version on pypi and also allow
passthrough of additional arguments

fixed fnparsers to make more sense

bumpde version up
minor updates, fixed seed-length in align.py
added support for CASAVA 1.8 FASTQ files

run_job didn't work, removed it from cTubes. Added a new converter "cat"
that reads files and decompresses them if needed. Fixed align.py to use
cat, so that it isn't broken. Updated to 0.9.3.6

recoded tubes using cython (cTubes). repaired align script to handle
single-end files
fixed bug with single-end read alignments
fixed iteration in read-mode of gzip files

fixed align.py, fastqtotab -- compression flag no long used,
interpreted automatically. use open_func not format to open file. added
a debug message to bowtie

Updated align.py to look for reference genome and emit warnings if not
found. Requires scripter 3.3.0
Fixed barcode processing, gzip file handling. both were somehow broken
bugfix. genome_build = None, not is None
bugfix: write config in call_peaks needs kwarg target_dir

Significantly speed improvements for preprocess_reads.py. Uses a C
extension now. Modified other modules to handle gzip files better; use
system gzip for speed when compressing output
Updated setup.py to use new freeze of MACS2

Many bugfixes, updated call_peaks to use new MACS2, may need more
updates when MACS2 is done

updated call_peaks to support changes to MACS2 (consolidation of
scripts). added permute_fasta to bioplus/fasta

added installation/requirements to documentation. changed setup.py to
using setuptools. it is now REQUIRED
added micro release number for alpha versions (0.9.0)
added MACS to requirements for installation

removed fetch_sequences.py in favor of twobitreader's new ability to run
as a script

added bedgraph.py, not currently used for anything
removed make_session, make_track_hub, sam_to_bam permanently
updated aligned.py, call_peaks.py to use new modified version of MACS

updated call_peaks and genometools for new version of MACS. started work
on make_track_hub. this will replace make_session

fetch_sequences is going to be deprecated and integrated into
call_peaks. most of the functionality has been integrated into
twobitreader package

call_peaks has been updated to rely exclusively on the new MACS2
package. right now only my github page has a working copy with all the
features
improved genometools a bit, correctly identifies BAM file genomes now

added genometools and database of genomes
	- gives chr names,sizes for a genome
	- currently contains UCSC genomes w/ < 100 chrs
	- can guess the genome from a BAM file

some bugfixes
renamed run_macs.py -> call_peaks.py
added some new functions silently to call_peaks.py
added modules to setup.py, fixed missing import in polledpipe.py

separated out some functionality into modules. started adding macs2 to
run_macs. will remove ppysam on next commit

small bugfixes to fetch_sequences
updated setup

added configuation support to preprocess reads
